hh3cFcTraceRoute.name: hh3cFcTraceRoute

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

hh3cFcTraceRoute.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cFcTraceRoute.description: This MIB module is for the management of the Fibre Channel Trace Route functionality.

hh3cFcTraceRouteTable.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteTable
hh3cFcTraceRouteTable.description: A table of trace route entries containing a group of trace route requests that need to be executed at the agent.

hh3cFcTraceRouteEntry.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteEntry
hh3cFcTraceRouteEntry.description: A trace route request entry that needs to be executed at the agent.

hh3cFcTraceRouteIndex.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteIndex
hh3cFcTraceRouteIndex.description: The index of the current trace route entry. This object uniquely identifies a trace route request entry in a specified VSAN (Virtual Storage Area Network).

hh3cFcTraceRouteVsan.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteVsan
hh3cFcTraceRouteVsan.description: The VSAN on which the trace route request will be executed. If the corresponding instance value of hh3cFcTraceRouteOperStatus is 'inProgress', the object cannot be modified.

hh3cFcTraceRouteAddressType.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteAddressType
hh3cFcTraceRouteAddressType.description: The type of the corresponding instance of hh3cFcTraceRouteAddress object.

hh3cFcTraceRouteAddress.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteAddress
hh3cFcTraceRouteAddress.description: The address to which the route will be traced. This object will contain an 8-octet WWN (World Wide Name), if the value of the associated instance of hh3cFcTraceRouteAddressType object is 'wwn'. This object will contain a 3-octet Fibre Channel ID, if the value of the associated instance of hh3cFcTraceRouteAddressType object is 'fcid'.

hh3cFcTraceRouteTimeout.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteTimeout
hh3cFcTraceRouteTimeout.description: The value of timeout for this trace route request. If the corresponding instance value of hh3cFcTraceRouteOperStatus object is 'inProgress', this object cannot be modified.

hh3cFcTraceRouteAdminStatus.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteAdminStatus
hh3cFcTraceRouteAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of each hh3cFcTraceRouteEntry. The object has two values: enable - Activate the entry. disable - Deactivate the entry. When the trace route entry is being executed, this object cannot be modified. If this object is being read, a value of 'enable' will be returned. When the execution finishes, the value of this object will be set to 'disable'.

hh3cFcTraceRouteOperStatus.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteOperStatus
hh3cFcTraceRouteOperStatus.description: This object indicates the operational status of this hh3cFcTraceRouteEntry. The value specifications are listed as follows: inProgress - Trace route is in progress. success - Trace route has succeeded. partialSuccess - Trace route has partially succeeded. failure - Trace route has failed due to resource limitations. disabled - Trace route is disabled.

hh3cFcTraceRouteAgeInterval.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteAgeInterval
hh3cFcTraceRouteAgeInterval.description: The interval time for an entry to age out after a trace route test is completed.

hh3cFcTraceRouteTrapOnCompletion.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteTrapOnCompletion
hh3cFcTraceRouteTrapOnCompletion.description: This object indicates whether a hh3cFcTraceRouteCompletionNotify notification should be generated when this trace route test completes.

hh3cFcTraceRouteRowStatus.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteRowStatus
hh3cFcTraceRouteRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsTable.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsTable
hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsTable.description: A table of trace route hop results. This table indicates the hop-by-hop result of a trace route test associated with an entry in the hh3cFcTraceRouteTable.

hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsEntry.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsEntry
hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsEntry.description: A trace route hop entry. The first index member specifies the hh3cFcTraceRouteEntry that an hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsEntry is associated with. The second index element identifies a hop in a trace route path. In the case of a complete path being traced, entries corresponding to an hh3cFcTraceRouteEntry are created automatically in this table. Each hop in the complete path will be listed in this table. When an hh3cFcTraceRouteEntry is deleted or aged out, the entries corresponding to the hh3cFcTraceRouteEntry in this table are also deleted.

hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsIndex.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsIndex
hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsIndex.description: This object indicates the hop index for a trace route hop. Values for this object associated with the same hh3cFcTraceRouteIndex MUST begin with 1 and automatically increase by 1.

hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsAddr.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsAddr
hh3cFcTraceRouteHopsAddr.description: This object specifies the WWN of the device associated with this hop.

hh3cFcTraceRouteCompletionNotify.name: hh3cFcTraceRouteCompletionNotify
hh3cFcTraceRouteCompletionNotify.description: When a trace route test is finished and the instance of hh3cFcTraceRouteTrapOnCompletion associated with the test is set to 'true', this notification occurred.
